nctions\n`f : E → F` and `g : E → G` (named `leftFun` and `rightFun`) and a point `a` (named `pt`) such that\n\n* both functions are strictly differentiable at `a`;\n* the derivatives are surjective;\n* the kernels of the derivatives are complementary subspaces of `E`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Implicit.html#ImplicitFunctionData","kind":"structure","line":94,"name":"ImplicitFunctionData","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Implicit.lean#L94-L118"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.InverseFunctionTheorem.FDeriv","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.FDeriv.Add","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.FDeriv.Prod","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Module.Complemented"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.Implicit"}